They are pretty similar in workload and difficulty. EE16B may be slightly more difficult, but not considerably. 

-------------

Just another perspective: I found 16B to be of significantly higher workload and difficulty (particularly 16B had longer/harder labs), but then again, your professor could affect this. I had Sahai/Pister/Roychowdhury in Spring 2019, for reference.

--------------

Third Perspective: 

EE16b was nearly 1.5-3 times as hard both conceptually and time-investment wise compared to 16a.... (at least with Sahai lol)

They are pretty similar in workload and difficulty. EE16B may be slightly more difficult, but not considerably.
